genresAdvancedInfo.name: go-go
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Go-go is a genre of music that originated in Washington, D.C. in the late 1960s. It is characterized by its use of funk, R&B, and soul music, combined with a distinctive percussion style known as "the pocket." Go-go music is often played live, with call-and-response vocals and improvisation. The genre is closely associated with the African American community in D.C. and has been influential in shaping the city's cultural identity.
